I've created the Image View developer guide at `image-view.md`. The document covers:

- **Creating an ImageView** - Factory methods and basic setup
- **Setting the Image Source** - Using `SetResourceUrl()` to load images
- **Fitting Modes** - Four fitting modes for controlling image scaling
- **Pixel Area and Cropping** - Displaying sub-regions with animatable pixel area
- **Image Color and Tinting** - Applying color multipliers for effects
- **Alpha Masking** - Shaping visible regions with mask images
- **Loading Policies** - Controlling when images load and unload
- **Placeholder Images** - Showing placeholders during loading
- **Sampling Mode and Desired Size** - Memory optimization and filtering control
- **Resource Ready Signal** - Receiving load completion notifications
- **N-Patch Images** - 9-patch stretching support

All API examples use only allowed symbols from the provided context pack, with fluent chaining style and `Dali::Ui::ImageView` as the app-facing object model.
